text: Anordiol, or anordriol, also known as 2α,17α-diethynyl-A- nor-5α-androstane-2β,17β-diol, is a synthetic steroid-like mixed estrogen and antiestrogen and an active metabolite of anordrin, a postcoital contraceptive that is marketed and used in China. Relative to anordrin, anordiol has similar but more potent actions. ==References== Category:Alkyne derivatives Category:Androstanes Category:Diols Category:Human drug metabolites Category:Selective estrogen receptor modulators Category:Synthetic estrogens
